üëã Hello Doctor. I'm your mammography analysis assistant.

I can:
‚Ä¢ Analyze your recent mammogram images

**Mammography - Technical Information:**

‚Ä¢ **Technique**: Low-dose breast X-ray (15-30 kV)
‚Ä¢ **Standard views**: Craniocaudal (CC) and Mediolateral oblique (MLO)
‚Ä¢ **Screening**: Recommended every 2 years for women 50-74
‚Ä¢ **Diagnostic**: Evaluation of symptoms or detected abnormalities

**Mammographic signs:**
‚Ä¢ **Masses**: Shape, margins, density evaluation
‚Ä¢ **Calcifications**: Distribution, morphology
‚Ä¢ **Architectural distortion**: Normal architecture alteration

*I can analyze your images to identify these signs.*

**Breast Density (BI-RADS Classification):**

‚Ä¢ **A - Almost entirely fatty**: High mammography sensitivity
‚Ä¢ **B - Scattered fibroglandular tissue**: Good sensitivity
‚Ä¢ **C - Heterogeneously dense**: May obscure small lesions
‚Ä¢ **D - Extremely dense**: Substantially reduces sensitivity

**Clinical impact:**
‚Ä¢ Dense breasts (C-D): 4-6x higher cancer risk
‚Ä¢ Complementary screening: Ultrasound or MRI recommended
‚Ä¢ Surveillance: Adapted according to risk level

*I can analyze density in your mammogram images.*
